<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="347" pageId="1" pageNumber="346" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,974,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,544,1082,1107]" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">Description. Apterous male.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[556,619,1083,1107]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">Color</emphasis>
. Most of body brown (
<figureCitation box="[906,977,1082,1107]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,373,1881]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mesovelia tuberculata sp. nov. (A) male, holotype, dorsal view; (B) male, holotype, ventral view; (C) male, holotype, lateral view; (D) female, paratype, dorsal view; (E) female, paratype, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254990/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Head with frons light brown, lateral margins brown, basal margin darker, cephalic trichobothria inserted in pits with dark brown borders; eyes reddish brown; antennae brown, basal 1/3 of antennomere I lighter; most of rostrum yellow, article IV brown. Pronotum yellow, with margins brown; mesonotum with central yellow spot. Coxae, trochanters, and basal 2/3 of femora light yellow; distal region of femora, tibiae and tarsi light brown. Abdominal tergum I with light spots laterally; tergum VII light yellow; tergum VIII light yellow, with posterior margin brown; connexivum brown or a little lighter; sternum VII with central light spot; sternum VIII and pygophore yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,974,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis box="[199,336,1334,1358]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">Morphology</emphasis>
. Body covered by short brown setae. Head covered by mainly short brown setae; clypeus covered by large brown setae; sides in front of eyes and area between clypeus and frons covered by silvery pubescence; antennae thin, very long, reaching middle of abdomen; antennomere I stout and curved outward; antennomeres III– IV narrower than I–II, antennomere I about 1.3 times longer than II, IV about 1.2 times longer than III; antennomere I with margins converging proximally and distally, antennomere II with margins diverging distally, III–IV with margins parallel; rostrum long, reaching first abdominal sternum. Pronotum with short collar behind head. Pro- and mesofemora subequal in length to pro- and mesotibiae, pro-, meso- and metafemora each with a large dark brown seta on dorsoposterior 1/6; meso- and metafemora each with another large dark brown seta on dorsoposterior 1/3, ventrally without row of spinules; pro-, meso- and metatibiae with row of longer dark brown setae not longer than pretarsal claw; metatibia about 1.3 times longer than metafemur. Abdominal tergum VII with posterior margin rounded; posterior margin of tergum VIII with weak notch; anterodorsal region of pleuron VIII with a tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[332,395,1730,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,373,1881]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mesovelia tuberculata sp. nov. (A) male, holotype, dorsal view; (B) male, holotype, ventral view; (C) male, holotype, lateral view; (D) female, paratype, dorsal view; (E) female, paratype, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254990/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
C); sternum VI with fringe of black spinules on rounded posteromedian projection (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1397,1730,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,373,1881]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mesovelia tuberculata sp. nov. (A) male, holotype, dorsal view; (B) male, holotype, ventral view; (C) male, holotype, lateral view; (D) female, paratype, dorsal view; (E) female, paratype, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254990/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
B); paramere with margins converging, posterior margin sharp, apex single (
<figureCitation box="[964,1030,1766,1791]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1485,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1485,1914]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Parameres. (A) M. amoena Uhler [modified from Spangler (1990)]; (B) M. mulsanti White [modified from Moreira et al. (2008)]; (C) M. zeteki Harris &amp; Drake; (D) M. tuberculata sp. nov.." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254992/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,974,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,406,1802,1827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="346">Apterous female.</emphasis>
Similar to male in color pattern, except connexiva yellow with brown mesal and lateral margins. Also similar in morphology, except genitalia and absence of fringe on posterior margin of abdominal sternum VI.
